Adding unlimited lines in a Text(Swift UI) or UILabel(Swift)
  UILabel in Swift
    var numberOfLines: Int { get set }
      To remove any maximum limit, and use as many lines as needed, set the value of this property to 0.
      ex: .numberOfLines = 0
  Text in Swift UI
    lineLimit(number: Int?)
      To remove any maximum limit, and use as many lines as needed, set the value of this property to nil.
      ex: .lineLimit(nil).fixedSize(horizontal: false, vertical: true)
      
